<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Spoon River College</h2>
<strong>Canton, IL</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>The Advanced Placement Program and associated tests are offered only in high schools.  Students who have participated in the AP program may be eligible to receive credit and advanced placement at Spoon River College on the basis of subject area examinations. Students wishing such credit should request the College Entrance Examination Board to send their AP scored examinations to the Admissions Office.  These scores will be evaluated and credit awarded based on scores adopted by the college faculty.  Students will be notified by the Registrar and have any credit which has been awarded placed on their transcript.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.src.edu/services/Documents/catalogs/2012-2013Catalog.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

